  array('id_index'=>8886,'id'=>246512,'name'=>'Signing Time','description'=>'Signing Time came about as one mother\'s journey to communicate with her deaf daughter; by teaching her baby, and learning signs herself, Rachel Coleman found that by eighteen months, her girl could sign sentences that most hearing children would find difficult at the same age. When her second daughter was born with spina bifida, Rachel discovered that baby sign language would help her communicate with children struggling with other challenges as well. Together with her sister, Rachel created an engaging, accessible video to educate hearing children in sign language.

